  "best_lb_obtained_caveat": "This is the bin-LP TV-only lower bound at d=10 from local search (SLSQP).  RIGOROUS unconditional LB on C_{1a}: yes (cascade derivation valid for any f).  However the local search may not find the GLOBAL min, so the true bin-LP value could be lower; the value 1.2259 is an UPPER ESTIMATE of the true bin-LP min, hence an UPPER ESTIMATE of one rigorous LB on C_{1a}.",
  "best_lb_diagnostic_w2_NOT_rigorous": 1.4123998555247725,
  "joint_min_TV_and_L4_NOT_RIGOROUS": 1.3634647947215737,
  "joint_min_caveat": "This 1.3635 is min over piecewise-constant f's (with bin masses mu) of max(maxTV(mu), ||hat f||_4^4(piecewise-const f)). It is NOT a rigorous LB on C_{1a} for general (non-piecewise-constant) f, because ||hat f||_4^4 depends on the within-bin shape of f, not just on mu.  Specifically, smoother f within bins can have SMALLER ||hat f||_4^4 than piecewise-constant.  Hence joint_min DOES NOT transfer to a rigorous LB on inf_f max(f*f).",
  "vs_1_2802": "below",
  "vs_mv_1_2748": "below",
  "promising": false,
  "verdict_short": "All RIGOROUS unconditional OT/Wasserstein angles tested fail to lift the LB above CS 1.2802 at d in {4,...,10}: bin-LP TV ~ 1.226 at d=10. The Plancherel L^4 bound on piecewise-constant f gives a within-class joint min of 1.3635 at d=8 BUT is not rigorous for general f (depends on within-bin shape). W_2(mu,U_d)<=R is diagnostic only (no Talagrand bound on f from max(f*f)). Symmetric L^2 trivially gives 2.0 but is useless for non-symmetric extremiser. Direction NEGATIVE.",
  "verdict_long": "Probed three OT/W_2 angles for rigorous lower bounds on C_{1a}: (A) bin-LP with W_2(mu, U_d) <= R constraint - DIAGNOSTIC ONLY, since the natural Talagrand/EPI chain runs the wrong way (small max(f*f) does NOT force f close to U: it controls the spread of f*f, not f). Numerically the constraint LIFTS the bin-LP min from ~1.226 (unconstrained) to ~1.412 (at R=0.005, d=8), because U_d itself has large max_W TV (~1.42 at d=8). But this is NOT a rigorous LB on C_{1a}. (B) Plancherel-derived ||hat f||_4^4 <= max(f*f), which IS unconditional for any specific f. We computed this for bin-LP-piecewise-constant f and joint-minimised max(maxTV, ||hat f||_4^4(piecewise-const)) - obtained 1.3635 at d=8. HOWEVER this is NOT a rigorous LB on C_{1a}: the ||hat f||_4^4 quantity depends on the within-bin shape of f, and smoother (non-piecewise-constant) f compatible with the same bin masses mu can have SMALLER ||hat f||_4^4. So 1.3635 is only a LB on inf_{piecewise-const f} max(f*f), not on inf_{general f} max(f*f). (C) Symmetric L^2 ||f||_2^2 <= max(f*f) via Cauchy-Schwarz at t=0 - gives the TRIVIAL 2.0 bound for symmetric f. The C_{1a} extremiser is non-symmetric (Sidon-like sparse spike construction), so the symmetric LB does not transfer. CONCLUSION: All RIGOROUS unconditional bounds are below 1.2802; rigorous OT-derived progress is NEGATIVE. The diagnostic and within-class results (1.41 W_2-restricted, 1.36 piecewise-const-restricted) do show that OT structure carries useful signal in restricted regimes, suggesting potential paths if (i) a separate concentration bound on f_opt can be proven OR (ii) an unconditional within-bin f-shape minimisation of ||hat f||_4^4 can be carried out at the variational level. Both are non-trivial future work.",
  "next_steps_if_promising": [
    "Compute inf_f ||hat f||_4^4 over f compatible with given bin masses mu - this is a calc-of-variations problem (Lagrangian on each bin) that would give a TRUE LB.  Probably yields values BELOW the joint min reported here, killing the bound.",
